Running command: export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"; (echo '{"jsonrpc": "2.0", "method": "prompt", "id": "1", "params": {"user_input": "You are an orchestrator for a **fan-out and synthesis** workflow.\n\nYour working directory is: /workspace\n\n## Rules\n- The task, required output format, save location, and decomposition guide are in your instruction above.\n- All input data files are in `/input_artifacts/`.\n- You have a Shell tool and a Task tool (to spawn sub-agents).\n- Sub-agents run in isolated contexts \u2014 include ALL necessary info in their prompts.\n\n## Workflow\n1. **Read your instruction** \u2014 understand the task, output requirements, and decomposition guide.\n2. **Fan-out phase**: Identify independent research/analysis threads. Spawn a sub-agent for each thread to work in parallel.\n3. **Collect**: Gather all sub-agent results.\n4. **Synthesis phase**: Integrate all perspectives into a unified output. Resolve contradictions, deduplicate findings, and produce a coherent answer.\n5. **Output**: Follow the output instructions exactly as specified in your task instruction.\n\n## Sub-Agent Instructions\n- Each sub-agent works on one independent thread/perspective.\n- They should NOT see each other'"'"'s work \u2014 that'"'"'s the point of independent analysis.\n- Spawn approximately 6 sub-agents for the fan-out phase.\n\n\n# Django Ticket #32365: zoneinfo should be the default\n\nWe'"'"'re doing the pytz -> zoneinfo migration for Django 4.0.\n\nThe codebase currently uses pytz as the default timezone implementation\nacross core utils, database backends, template tags, docs, and tests.\nWe need to flip that so zoneinfo is the default path.\n\n- zoneinfo (or backports.zoneinfo on older Python) replaces pytz everywhere.\n- pytz is no longer a hard dependency.\n- django.utils.timezone.utc should use the standard library UTC.\n- Add a transitional setting so existing projects can keep using pytz\n  temporarily. Overriding it should trigger a deprecation warning since\n  pytz support will be removed in Django 5.0.\n- The is_dst parameter should be deprecated wherever it currently appears\n  in timezone-aware functions. It should raise a deprecation warning and\n  no longer default to None.\n- Update all relevant documentation and tests.\n\nConstraints:\n\n- Work in `/testbed`.\n- Do not modify files outside the Django source tree and its tests.\n- Do not modify `tests/runtests.py` or the test runner infrastructure.\n\n\n## Gold Decomposition Guide\nsub_tasks:\n  - id: core-timezone-utils\n    description: >\n      Own /testbed/django/utils/timezone.py. Currently it imports pytz\n      unconditionally and uses pytz.utc everywhere. After your changes:\n      the file must import zoneinfo (not pytz) at module level, remove\n      any unconditional '"'"'import pytz'"'"', set utc to datetime.timezone.utc,\n      use zoneinfo.ZoneInfo for timezone construction, and fall back to\n      pytz only when USE_DEPRECATED_PYTZ is True. The is_dst parameter\n      on make_aware() must emit a deprecation warning and its default\n      value must no longer be None.\n      Do not modify tests, docs, DB backends, or settings files.\n    depends_on: []\n    parallel_group: fan-out\n\n  - id: settings-and-config\n    description: >\n      Own /testbed/django/conf/ and /testbed/setup.cfg. Add a\n      USE_DEPRECATED_PYTZ setting (default False) that emits a deprecation\n      warning when overridden. In setup.cfg, remove pytz as a hard install\n      dependency and add backports.zoneinfo as a conditional dependency for\n      Python < 3.9 and tzdata for Windows.\n      Do not modify tests, docs, or other source files.\n    depends_on: []\n    parallel_group: fan-out\n\n  - id: db-backends-and-models\n    description: >\n      Own Django source files under /testbed/django/db/,\n      /testbed/django/templatetags/, and\n      /testbed/django/contrib/admin/templatetags/. Currently these layers\n      use pytz directly for timezone construction. After your changes:\n      both backends/base/base.py and backends/sqlite3/base.py should use\n      zoneinfo by default and reference USE_DEPRECATED_PYTZ for the pytz\n      fallback path \u2014 neither should have an unconditional pytz import.\n      The migration serializer (db/migrations/serializer.py) must not\n      produce pytz-specific representations like <UTC>.\n      templatetags/tz.py must import zoneinfo instead of pytz and handle\n      both ZoneInfoNotFoundError and pytz.UnknownTimeZoneError.\n      is_dst parameters in Trunc functions (db/models/functions/datetime.py)\n      and datetimes() (db/models/query.py) must no longer default to None.\n      Do not modify tests or docs.\n    depends_on: []\n    parallel_group: fan-out\n\n  - id: documentation\n    description: >\n      Own all files under /testbed/docs/. Update at minimum:\n      releases/4.0.txt, internals/deprecation.txt, ref/settings.txt,\n      topics/i18n/timezones.txt, ref/utils.txt, and\n      ref/models/database-functions.txt. After your changes, docs should\n      describe zoneinfo as the default, document USE_DEPRECATED_PYTZ, and\n      mark is_dst as deprecated. Do not modify any Python source or test\n      files.\n    depends_on: []\n    parallel_group: fan-out\n\n  - id: test-updates\n    description: >\n      Own all files under /testbed/tests/. Currently the tests assume pytz\n      is always available and is the default. After your changes, zoneinfo\n      should be the default in all tests, pytz imports should be\n      conditional, and there should be coverage for USE_DEPRECATED_PYTZ\n      and is_dst deprecation warnings. Do not modify Django source or docs.\n    depends_on: []\n    parallel_group: fan-out\n\n  - id: integration-verify\n    description: >\n      After all other agents finish, run these Django test suites:\n      utils_tests.test_timezone, settings_tests, timezones, datetimes,\n      migrations.test_writer. If any tests fail, diagnose and fix \u2014 pay\n      special attention to serializer output format and template tag error\n      handling for invalid timezone names.\n    depends_on:\n      - core-timezone-utils\n      - settings-and-config\n      - db-backends-and-models\n      - documentation\n      - test-updates\n    parallel_group: synthesize\n"}}'; sleep 86400) | kimi --config-file /tmp/kimi-config.json --wire --yolo 2>/dev/null | (while IFS= read -r line; do echo "$line" >> /logs/agent/kimi-cli.txt; case "$line" in *'"id":"1"'*) break ;; esac; done; kill 0 2>/dev/null)
